Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three driver-tracking endpoints (vehicles list, GPS update, stop) plus
two transport-attendance endpoints (roster, bulk mark) wired into the
mobile API. Without these the driver tab in the app silently 404s on
every GPS push and the vehicle picker never populates.

Routes (all under /api/mobile/, behind auth:sanctum + tenant):
- GET  /transport/driver/vehicles           → list of vehicles assigned
                                              to the logged-in driver/
                                              conductor
- POST /transport/driver-tracking/update    → live GPS push (10s loop)
- POST /transport/driver-tracking/stop      → mark vehicle offline
- GET  /transport/attendance/students       → roster for a route+date+
                                              trip with current status
- POST /transport/attendance/mark           → bulk-save boarding /
                                              drop-off attendance,
                                              fires parent notifications
                                              via NotificationService

DriverTrackingController gets a new assignedVehicles() method that
filters to driver_id OR conductor_id matches and returns a flat shape
the mobile UI expects (id, vehicle_number, route_name, capacity).

MobileApiController gets transportAttendanceStudents() and
transportAttendanceMark() — JSON twins of the existing web
TransportAttendanceController. Driver/conductor scope is enforced; a
driver can only mark students on routes their assigned vehicles run.

